{"by":"wonger_","id":47774016,"parent":47729327,"text":"I like the AAA WCAG recommendation. I&#x27;d also recommend from my casual experience listening to lots of old people...<p>- a large font size by default, and maybe a font size slider on the homepage. Test everything at 200-300% scale as WCAG recommends<p>- don&#x27;t change the UI! Or change as little as possible, at least for existing users. Which kinda upturns the whole always-updating nature of web SaaS but I think it can be done<p>- hire a good designer who can streamline your UX and screens and keep only the bare minimum features<p>- maybe offer human support? Like a phone number? Probably unreasonable for you tho<p>Wish I had ideas for simpler login and auth.<p>Have you found any successful design strategies in your 10 years? Any insights from user testing?","time":1776220562,"type":"comment"}